itational interactions with satellites; ($iv$) the\nfraction of barred galaxies grows rapidly at high redshift and stabilizes below\n$z\\sim 2$, except for the most massive galaxies that show a decrease in the bar\noccupation fraction at low redshift; ($v$) galaxies with $M_{*} \\sim\n10^{11}~{\\rm M_{\\odot}}$ exhibit the highest relative occurrence of bars at\n$z=0$, in agreement with observational studies. We publicly release MORDOR and\nthe morphological catalogue of TNG50 galaxies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 9 Jun 2022 18:00:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 8 Jul 2022 18:00:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-07-12"}
